'''Gail Haraven''' is a writer from Israel. She is the author of six novels and three short story collections, as well as plays and nonfiction. She was awarded the prestigious [[Sapir Prize for Literature]] for ''The Confessions of Noa Weber'', and currently lives in Jerusalem. ''The Confessions of Noa Weber'' is her first book translated into English <ref>http://www.amazon.com/Confessions-Noa-Weber-Gail-Hareven/dp/1933633689/ref=pd_bbs_sr_1?ie=UTF8&s=books&qid=1235412451&sr=8-1</ref> and it won the 2009 [[Best Translated Book Award]].

== Bibliography ==

*''The Confessions of Noa Weber'', (2009) [[Melville House Publishing]]

